我幫不了你多少忙的
I wouldn't be very useful to you.

175
00:13:03,632 --> 00:13:05,065
我不再想那些事了
I don't think about it anymore.

176
00:13:05,134 --> 00:13:07,796
是嗎？你最後抓到的那兩個
Really? The last two we had, you caught.

177
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:10,532
你和其它人也能做到
By doing what you and the other guys are doing.

178
00:13:10,639 --> 00:13:13,107
事實不是這樣，是你自己這樣想
That's not entirely true. It's the way you think.

179
00:13:13,175 --> 00:13:16,838
拜託，關於我怎麼想的八卦已經夠多了
Come on. There's been a lot of bullshit about the way I think.

180
00:13:16,946 --> 00:13:19,141
我已經找到技術人員分析證據
I've got technicians to examine evidence...

181
00:13:19,214 --> 00:13:20,613
但是我們還需要你
but you've got that other thing.

182
00:13:20,683 --> 00:13:23,982
想像投射，隨你怎麼說
Imagination. Projection. Whatever.

183
00:13:24,219 --> 00:13:27,882
我知道你不喜歡這樣   你也不喜歡
- I know you don't like it. - You wouldn't like it, either.

184
00:13:42,801 --> 00:13:46,293
[Moving instrumental music]

185
00:13:50,212 --> 00:13:52,442
這個神經病在二月二十五號滿月那天…
This freak killed the Jacobis in Birmingham...

186
00:13:52,514 --> 00:13:54,948
殺死住在伯明翰的傑可比一家人
on Saturday night, February 25. Full moon.

187
00:13:55,050 --> 00:13:57,179
三月二十八號，幾天前，在亞特蘭大…
He killed the Leeds family in Atlanta...

188
00:13:57,186 --> 00:13:58,814
殺死立茲一家人
a few nights ago, March 28.

189
00:13:58,821 --> 00:14:00,345
就在滿月的前一天
One day short of a lunar month.

190
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:02,947
如果我們運氣夠好，在他再度下手之前…
If we're lucky, we may have a little over three weeks...

191
00:14:03,025 --> 00:14:05,152
我們還有三個多禮拜的時間
before he does it again.

192
00:14:05,227 --> 00:14:07,525
威爾，你相信我的判斷嗎？
Will, do you respect my judgment?

193
00:14:09,231 --> 00:14:10,425
當然
Of course.

194
00:14:10,499 --> 00:14:14,026
我想有你幫忙，我們能更快逮到他
I think we have a better chance to catch him fast if you help.

195
00:14:14,169 --> 00:14:16,729
到亞特蘭大一趟看看就好
Go to Atlanta and look. Just look.

196
00:14:17,439 --> 00:14:20,033
然後幫我對當地警察做簡報，就這樣
Then help me brief the locals. That's it.

197
00:14:21,276 --> 00:14:23,301
克勞佛有整個政府單位在幫他
MOLLY: Crawford has the whole damn government.

198
00:14:23,379 --> 00:14:24,676
幹嘛還需要你？
Why does he need you?

199
00:14:24,747 --> 00:14:27,409
他只是希望我看看一些證據，莫莉
He just wants me to look at some evidence, Molly.

200
00:14:27,516 --> 00:14:29,780
給他不同看法
Give him another point of view.

201
00:14:30,452 --> 00:14:33,615
只要幾天，頂多一個禮拜，辦完我馬上回來
It's a few days, a week maybe, and I'll be right back.

202
00:14:33,722 --> 00:14:35,952
你相信他？　　我相信
- And you believed that? - Yes.

203
00:14:37,559 --> 00:14:40,187
這樣的案子非常少…
These kinds of cases come up very rarely...

204
00:14:40,262 --> 00:14:41,661
我有過經驗
and I've had experience.

205
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:43,425
對，你有
Yes, you have.

206
00:14:45,034 --> 00:14:47,059
你做的夠多了，威爾
You're paid up, Will.

207
00:14:47,403 --> 00:14:50,065
我們都是，連喬許都付出代價
All of us. Even Josh.

208
00:14:51,740 --> 00:14:55,403
這是一個我可以幫他們救人的機會
There's a chance I could help them save some lives.

209
00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:58,037
我怎麼能拒絕？
How do I say no to that?

210
00:15:06,255 --> 00:15:09,383
這個殺人犯不會看到我，或知道我的名字
This one will never see me or know my name.

211
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:13,228
我只是幫他們找到他
I'll just help them find him.

212
00:15:13,295 --> 00:15:15,525
那些警察會去逮他，不是我
The cops will take him down, not me.

213
00:15:20,769 --> 00:15:23,533
我不負責調查這個案子，莫莉，我保證
I'll be in the back of the pack, Molly, I promise.

214
00:15:23,605 --> 00:15:25,505
你從來做不到
Never in your life.

215
00:15:26,605 --> 00:15:28,095
[Tender instrumental music]

216
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:32,477
我瞭解你   別這樣，來
- I know you. - Come on. Come here.

217
00:15:37,286 --> 00:15:38,719
我愛你
WILL: I love you.

218
00:15:38,787 --> 00:15:41,017
我幾天以後就回來   好
WILL: See you in a few days. JOSH: Okay.

219
00:15:41,490 --> 00:15:43,458
我晚上打電話給你
WILL: I'll call you tonight.

220
00:15:47,792 --> 00:15:49,953
[Car engine starts up]

221
00:15:54,203 --> 00:15:56,103
爸爸，再見！
JOSH: 'Bye, Dad!

222
00:15:59,738 --> 00:16:03,230
[Melancholy instrumental music]

223
00:16:07,015 --> 00:16:10,482
（喬治亞州，亞特蘭大，立茲家）
Leeds House, Atlanta, Georgia

224
00:16:25,063 --> 00:16:28,555
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

225
00:16:30,305 --> 00:16:33,297
狗到哪兒去了？沒有人聽到狗叫聲
Where's the dog? No one heard barking.

226
00:16:33,809 --> 00:16:36,573
在檔案裡並沒有提到這部份
There's nothing about it in the case file.

227
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:05,892
[Tense instrumental music]

228
00:18:12,804 --> 00:18:16,672
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

229
00:18:18,743 --> 00:18:22,235
[Dramatic instrumental music]

230
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:49,003
闖入者摸黑進來，並割斷查理立茲的喉嚨
The intruder enters in the dark and cuts Charles Leeds' throat.

231
00:18:49,311 --> 00:18:52,280
當凡爾莉立茲要起身時，他開槍射中她腹部…
He shoots Valerie Leeds in the stomach as she's rising...

232
00:18:52,347 --> 00:18:54,781
讓她無法行動，但沒有殺死她
disabling her but not killing her.

233
00:18:56,485 --> 00:18:58,885
他讓她活活地看著她老公死…
He leaves her to watch her husband die...

234
00:18:59,321 --> 00:19:01,846
然後轉身來到走廊
then turns and goes down the hall.

235
00:19:15,066 --> 00:19:18,399
[Eerie instrumental music]

236
00:19:27,049 --> 00:19:28,983
小孩…
The children were....

237
00:19:32,487 --> 00:19:35,149
當他射殺小孩時，小孩正在床上睡覺…
The children were still in bed when they were shot...

238
00:19:35,223 --> 00:19:38,317
或許可以解釋他用的是滅音器
which might indicate that he used a silencer.

239
00:19:46,368 --> 00:19:50,099
他把屍體拖到主臥室，但是為什麼？
He dragged the bodies into the master bedroom, but why?

240
00:19:50,839 --> 00:19:54,400
他們都死了而且沒有人像…
They were already dead and none of them got the same...

241
00:19:55,344 --> 00:19:58,040
立茲太太一樣受辱
extra attention as Mrs. Leeds.

242
00:20:26,271 --> 00:20:28,432
[Dramatic instrumental music]

243
00:20:28,410 --> 00:20:30,401
一小片鏡子碎片插入…
Small pieces of mirror were inserted...

244
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:33,141
被害人的眼窩
in the orbital sockets of the victims.

245
00:20:33,548 --> 00:20:35,641
是在他們死後才插入
This occurred post-mortem.

246
00:20:45,427 --> 00:20:49,123
你為什麼要把鏡子放在他們的眼睛裡？
Why did you put mirrors in their eyes?

247
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:53,427
（希爾頓）

248
00:21:33,304 --> 00:21:34,965
[Warped child's cry]

249
00:21:35,473 --> 00:21:37,964
[Climactic instrumental music]

250
00:21:51,923 --> 00:21:52,753
[Gunshot]

251
00:21:52,824 --> 00:21:54,314
[Fabric tearing]

252
00:21:54,392 --> 00:21:55,882
[Heartbeats]

253
00:22:00,302 --> 00:22:01,295
這些小碎片的鏡子…
The pieces of mirror are to make their eyes look alive!

254
00:22:01,302 --> 00:22:03,695
是要讓他們的眼睛看起來栩栩如生！

255
00:22:03,705 --> 00:22:07,368
他要觀眾，他要他們通通排排站…
He wanted an audience. He wanted them all lined up...

256
00:22:07,476 --> 00:22:09,967
看著他摸她
watching him when he touched her.

257
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:13,745
當他摸她時
When he touched her.

258
00:22:17,486 --> 00:22:20,751
摸她，爽身粉
Touched. Talcum powder.

259
00:22:20,856 --> 00:22:22,881
有爽身粉
There was talcum powder.

260
00:22:25,093 --> 00:22:26,458
（原始資料）

261
00:22:26,528 --> 00:22:29,497
「立茲太太的右大腿內側有爽身粉的痕跡
WILL: "Mrs. Leeds had traces of talcum on her right inner thigh.

262
00:22:29,564 --> 00:22:30,861
「徹底搜查後…
"A complete search of the home...

263
00:22:30,932 --> 00:22:33,730
「在屋子裡並沒有發現相同的爽身粉」
"led to no such matching talcum in the house."

264
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:39,270
你把手套脫下來，是不是？你這狗娘養的！
You took your gloves off, didn't you? You son of a bitch!

265
00:22:40,208 --> 00:22:42,301
你把手套脫下來，用你的手…
You took your gloves off, touched her...

266
00:22:42,377 --> 00:22:44,106
摸她、並且殺死她
with your bare hand and wiped her down.

267
00:22:44,179 --> 00:22:48,205
但你脫下手套時，有沒有張開她的眼睛？
But when the gloves were off, did you open her eyes?

268
00:22:48,079 --> 00:22:51,242
[Telephone rings]

269
00:22:55,357 --> 00:22:56,346
克勞佛
Crawford.

270
00:22:56,424 --> 00:22:59,120
立茲一家人的屍體是不是還在停屍間？
WILL: Are the Leeds' bodies still at the morgue?

271
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:01,524
誰對找出潛藏的指紋很行？
Who's good with latent prints here?

272
00:23:01,596 --> 00:23:02,790
亞特蘭大警局
CRAWFORD: Atlanta P.D.

273
00:23:02,864 --> 00:23:04,525
他們找遍屍體上的指紋
They've already printed the bodies.

274
00:23:04,599 --> 00:23:06,965
不在屍體上，告訴他們檢查眼睛
Not the bodies. Tell them to check the eyes.

275
00:23:07,035 --> 00:23:09,595
立茲太太的眼睛，甚至是她的眼角膜
Mrs. Leeds' eyes. Even her corneas.

276
00:23:09,971 --> 00:23:13,873
我想他把手套脫下來，我想他碰過她
I think he took his gloves off. I think he had to touch her.

277
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:16,270
天啊，威爾
Jesus, Will.

278
00:23:16,344 --> 00:23:17,675
（亞特蘭大警局總部）

279
00:23:17,746 --> 00:23:19,407
各位先生，女士
PRINCI: Gentlemen. Ladies.

280
00:23:19,481 --> 00:23:21,779
這是兇手牙齒的樣子
This is what the subject's teeth look like.

281
00:23:21,883 --> 00:23:25,216
這個是留在立茲太太身上的咬痕
The impressions came from bite marks on Mrs. Leeds.

282
00:23:26,121 --> 00:23:28,419
這個彎曲的程度…
This degree of crookedness...

283
00:23:28,890 --> 00:23:31,654
加上中間門牙的溝槽…
plus the groove in this central incisor...

284
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:33,894
讓他的咬痕非常特別
makes his bite signature unique.

285
00:23:33,962 --> 00:23:35,862
他媽的像鯊魚
Fuckin' shark.

286
00:23:36,431 --> 00:23:38,058
住嘴！
SPRINGFIELD: Knock it off!

287
00:23:39,301 --> 00:23:41,235
我們很高興有FBI的幫忙
We're grateful to have the FBI.

288
00:23:41,303 --> 00:23:43,134
他們在這個領域裡有很多專家
They have a lot of expertise in this area.

289
00:23:43,204 --> 00:23:45,229
特別是調查員葛蘭姆
In particular, Investigator Graham does.

290
00:23:45,307 --> 00:23:46,672
是吧，傑克？
That right, Jack?

291
00:23:46,741 --> 00:23:48,402
是，長官
Yes, sir.

292
00:23:48,476 --> 00:23:51,172
葛蘭姆先生，你有什麼要補充的嗎？
Anything you want to add, Mr. Graham?

293
00:23:51,279 --> 00:23:54,146
請你到前面來好嗎？
COMMISSIONER: Why don't you come on up to the front, please?

294
00:23:56,084 --> 00:23:58,018
就是他   是嗎？
[Cops murmur]

295
00:23:58,086 --> 00:24:00,486
對就是他逮到萊克特
COP 1: That's the guy. COP 2: Was he?

296
00:24:00,589 --> 00:24:02,181
我以為他退休了
COP 3: Yeah, that's the guy who arrested Lecter.

297
00:24:02,257 --> 00:24:05,158
那個畜牲差一點就把他吃了
COP 4: I thought he retired.

298
00:24:03,387 --> 00:24:06,288
COP 5: The son of a bitch just about gutted him.

299
00:24:10,432 --> 00:24:13,868
立茲太太和傑科比太太是主要目標
Mrs. Leeds and Mrs. Jacobi were the primary targets.

300
00:24:14,035 --> 00:24:17,436
其它被殺的人只是為滿足他的幻想
The others were killed just to complete his fantasy.

301
00:24:17,539 --> 00:24:20,770
現在，我知道要接受這個事實對你們很難
WILL: I know that might be hard to accept given what you saw...

302
00:24:20,842 --> 00:24:22,867
但是這不是偶發事件
but this was not random.

303
00:24:22,978 --> 00:24:26,937
他不像有些殺人狂，他從來不會失控
This wasn't some killing frenzy. He was never out of control.

304
00:24:27,682 --> 00:24:31,174
這些攻擊都是計劃好的，他小心地挑選女人
These attacks were organized, the women carefully chosen.

305
00:24:31,286 --> 00:24:33,914
我們不知道他為什麼、又是如何找上她們
We don't know how he's choosing them, or why.

306
00:24:33,989 --> 00:24:36,685
她們住在不同州，而且彼此未曾謀面
They lived in different states and never met.

307
00:24:36,791 --> 00:24:38,725
但是還是有一些關聯
But there is some connection.

308
00:24:38,793 --> 00:24:41,956
有一些共同的原因，而且是關鍵
There's some common factor, and that's the key.

309
00:24:42,364 --> 00:24:45,128
找到這些關鍵因素，我們就能救人
Find out what that is, and we'll save lives.

310
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:48,533
否則，這種案子會一直持續下去…
'Cause this one is gonna go on and on...

311
00:24:48,703 --> 00:24:51,399
除非我們變聰明，或是我們運氣好
until we get smart or we get lucky.

312
00:24:53,041 --> 00:24:55,009
他是不會罷休的
He won't stop.

313
00:24:55,810 --> 00:24:58,904
為什麼？　　因為他覺得他是上帝
- Why not? - Because it makes him God.

314
00:25:00,415 --> 00:25:02,406
你會放棄嗎？
Would you give that up?

315
00:25:04,052 --> 00:25:07,818
你問到狗，昨晚一個獸醫打電話給我們
You asked about the dog. Last night a vet called us.

316
00:25:08,023 --> 00:25:10,685
立茲和他的大兒子…在他們被殺前的…
Leeds and his oldest boy brought the dog in...

317
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:12,659
那個下午…帶狗去他那裡
the afternoon before they were killed.

318
00:25:12,727 --> 00:25:15,025
那隻狗的肚子被刺破了
Had a puncture wound to its abdomen.

319
00:25:15,096 --> 00:25:16,859
獸醫只好讓它安樂死
The vet had to put it down.

320
00:25:16,931 --> 00:25:19,263
那隻狗的狗環上有地址嗎？
Was it wearing a collar with the address on it?

321
00:25:19,367 --> 00:25:20,925
沒有
No.

322
00:25:21,603 --> 00:25:24,538
傑科比一家有養狗嗎？　　沒有
- Did the Jacobis have a dog? - No dog.

323
00:25:24,606 --> 00:25:26,597
他們在地下室發現了個小箱子…
They found a litter box in the basement...

324
00:25:26,675 --> 00:25:29,041
有貓的糞便，但是沒有貓
cat droppings in it, no cat.

325
00:25:30,945 --> 00:25:35,074
如果貓被攻擊了，傑科比一家人可能已經把它埋了
If the cat was attacked, the Jacobis may have buried it.

326
00:25:35,617 --> 00:25:38,347
要伯明翰警局到後院搜尋
Ask Birmingham to check that backyard.

327
00:25:38,420 --> 00:25:41,719
告訴他們…使用甲烷比較快
And tell them to use a methane probe, it's faster.

328
00:25:41,919 --> 00:25:43,910
[Telephone rings]

329
00:25:44,459 --> 00:25:48,122
是的，你的電話
Yeah. It's for you.

330
00:25:50,098 --> 00:25:51,725
克勞佛
Crawford.

331
00:25:55,303 --> 00:25:57,635
卡爾，你是我的救星
Carl, you're the light of my life.

332
00:25:57,872 --> 00:25:59,567
這在法院成立嗎？
Would it hold up in court?

333
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:01,404
太好了
Okay. Great work.

334
00:26:03,111 --> 00:26:05,845
他們在立茲太太的眼睛發現指紋
They found a print on Mrs. Leeds' eye. Partial thumb.

335
00:26:05,861 --> 00:26:07,145
是大拇指的一部份

336
00:26:08,416 --> 00:26:10,884
除此之外，無可奉告
Besides that, there's nothing else to tell you.

337
00:26:10,952 --> 00:26:12,010
謝謝你們
Thank you for your time.

338
00:26:12,087 --> 00:26:13,748
我不能再多說什麼了
COMMISSIONER: I can't answer more questions.

339
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:16,052
威爾葛蘭姆！記得我嗎？
Will Graham! Remember me?

340
00:26:16,758 --> 00:26:20,717
佛瑞迪勞茲，我為《傳聞報》報導萊克特的案子
Freddy Lounds. I covered the Lecter case for the Tattler.

341
00:26:20,929 --> 00:26:22,897
也出了本相關的書   我記得
- Did the paperback. - Yeah, I remember.

342
00:26:22,964 --> 00:26:25,660
你何時加入這個案子的？有什麼線索嗎？
When did they bring you in? What've you got?

343
00:26:25,734 --> 00:26:29,135
你覺得這個牙仙會比萊克特厲害嗎？
You think the Tooth Fairy will be bigger than Lecter?

344
00:26:29,237 --> 00:26:31,671
我是說，他已經破了萊克特的紀錄…
I mean, he's already beaten Lecter's score...

345
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:32,732
你寫的儘是些狗屎
You write lying shit, and the Tattler is an asswipe!

346
00:26:32,740 --> 00:26:34,732
《傳聞報》不過用來當衛生紙！

347
00:26:34,809 --> 00:26:36,743
你離我遠一點
You stay away from me.

348
00:26:37,078 --> 00:26:38,841
走開，勞茲
Get away, Lounds.

349
00:26:40,482 --> 00:26:42,473
來個獨家怎麼樣？
How about an exclusive?

350
00:26:45,253 --> 00:26:46,914
對不起
Sorry about that.

351
00:26:47,021 --> 00:26:50,184
這個傢伙溜進醫院拍我
That guy snuck into the hospital and took those pictures of me.

352
00:26:50,291 --> 00:26:52,452
記不記得？我身上插了一堆管子？
Remember? With the tubes hanging out of me?

353
00:26:52,527 --> 00:26:54,119
別理這種人渣
Forget that prick.

354
00:26:54,195 --> 00:26:55,685
給自己一點信心
CRAWFORD: Give yourself some credit.

355
00:26:55,764 --> 00:26:57,527
只要我們逮到那個牙仙…
When we catch the Tooth Fairy...

356
00:26:57,599 --> 00:27:00,261
指紋加上咬痕，一定會讓他定罪
that print plus his teeth will burn him.

357
00:27:00,702 --> 00:27:02,192
你發現的，威爾
You did that, Will.

358
00:27:02,270 --> 00:27:04,295
證據就在那裡，傑克
That evidence was there, Jack.

359
00:27:04,806 --> 00:27:08,765
證據就在那裡，給大家看   但沒人看見
- It was there for anyone to see. - But nobody else did.

360
00:27:08,843 --> 00:27:11,209
我只是想說，你做得非常好
All I'm sayin' is, that was very good work.

361
00:27:11,312 --> 00:27:14,042
不，真正做的好是要看透整件事…
No, good work would be seeing it all the way through...

362
00:27:14,149 --> 00:27:15,616
並且逮到他
and catching the guy.

363
00:27:15,683 --> 00:27:19,119
我做不到，我只是做到你要我做的
And I can't do that. I did what you asked me to do.

364
00:27:19,721 --> 00:27:21,484
我要回家了
I'm going home.

365
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:25,386
我甚至完全不知道這個人究竟是誰
I don't even have any idea who this guy is.

366
00:27:25,493 --> 00:27:27,529
我剛剛只是給他們非常粗略的簡報
What I just gave them was broad strokes. He's got no face to me.

367
00:27:27,543 --> 00:27:28,979
我想像不出他是怎樣的人

368
00:27:28,997 --> 00:27:31,898
你辦葛雷特哈柏的案子時，也是這樣說？
That's what you said about Garrett Hobbs, remember?

369
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:34,560
然後你弄清楚了   不，我沒有
- And you figured him out. - No, I didn't.

370
00:27:34,669 --> 00:27:37,399
你沒有？　　沒有，我困在哈柏的案子裡
- You didn't? - No, I was stuck on Hobbs.

371
00:27:39,407 --> 00:27:41,102
有人幫我
I had help.

372
00:27:45,346 --> 00:27:47,041
是萊克特
From Lecter.

373
00:27:49,250 --> 00:27:50,740
對
WILL: Yeah.

374
00:27:55,356 --> 00:27:58,553
傑克，別和我玩把戲，不要這樣
Jack, don't play games with me. Don't do it.

375
00:27:59,694 --> 00:28:01,491
告訴我，你在想什麼
Just tell me what's on your mind.

376
00:28:01,563 --> 00:28:02,499
我要說的是…
I'm saying maybe we've got a resource we should look into.

377
00:28:02,513 --> 00:28:04,999
也許從他那裡我們會獲得調查的線索

378
00:28:05,066 --> 00:28:06,590
搞半天這就是你要的？
Is that what this was about?

379
00:28:06,668 --> 00:28:08,693
你是不是一開始就想問我？
Did you just want to ask me that all along?

380
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:11,034
別對我發火，這是我的工作
Don't get mad at me. I'm just doing my job.

381
00:28:11,105 --> 00:28:13,505
如果你有快捷方式…讓我知道
If you know a better shortcut, let me know it.

382
00:28:13,575 --> 00:28:16,043
如果你覺得他有任何可能，會對我說…
If you think there's any chance he'll talk to me...

383
00:28:16,110 --> 00:28:17,805
我自己去
I'll go myself.

384
00:28:19,247 --> 00:28:23,513
如果你辦不到，我會瞭解的
If you can't handle it, God knows I'd understand that.

385
00:28:30,725 --> 00:28:34,684
身為一個研究對象，萊克特讓我們很失望
CHILTON: As a research subject, Lecter has proven most disappointing.

386
00:28:35,230 --> 00:28:38,563
心理測驗對他起不了一點作用
He's simply impenetrable to psychological testing.

387
00:28:38,867 --> 00:28:41,427
羅沙哈性格測驗，主題統覺
Rorschach, Thematic Apperception.

388
00:28:41,769 --> 00:28:43,737
他都拿來折紙鶴
He folds them into origami.

389
00:28:43,805 --> 00:28:45,033
（奇爾頓）

390
00:28:45,106 --> 00:28:46,801
如你所見
CHILTON: As you see.

391
00:28:47,742 --> 00:28:50,040
你的小小造訪在我的同事間…
So you can imagine the stir your little visit...

392
00:28:50,111 --> 00:28:52,341
所帶來的刺激，葛蘭姆先生
is causing among my staff, Mr. Graham.

393
00:28:53,648 --> 00:28:55,912
如果你願意分享一點灼見…
If you'd care to share some insights...

394
00:28:55,984 --> 00:28:56,915
奇爾頓醫師，對不起…
Dr. Chilton, I'm sorry, I've got a 4:17 flight back to Atlanta.

395
00:28:56,934 --> 00:28:59,215
我要趕4點17分的飛機回亞特蘭大

396
00:28:59,287 --> 00:29:00,845
當然
Of course.

397
00:29:03,925 --> 00:29:06,655
告訴我，當你看到被萊克特謀殺的人…
Tell me, when you saw Lecter's murders...

398
00:29:06,761 --> 00:29:08,388
他們的樣子，所以…
their style, so to speak...

399
00:29:08,463 --> 00:29:11,921
你有可能重建他的幻想世界嗎？
were you able, perhaps, to reconstruct his fantasies?

400
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,969
如果有，你有記下任何東西嗎？
And, if so, did you jot down any impressions?

401
00:29:15,069 --> 00:29:16,627
沒有
WILL: No.

402
00:29:23,678 --> 00:29:25,509
坦白說，葛蘭姆先生
Let me be frank, Mr. Graham.

403
00:29:25,580 --> 00:29:27,614
萊克特的第一手分析資料
The first analysis of Lecter will be a publisher's wet dream.

404
00:29:27,630 --> 00:29:29,914
是出版商夢寐以求的內容

405
00:29:29,984 --> 00:29:32,612
我會歸功於你，當然
I'd give you full credit, of course.

406
00:29:36,424 --> 00:29:39,951
該死，你一定有些建議，你逮到他的
Damn it, man. You must have some advice. You caught him.

407
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:41,996
你怎麼辦到的？
What was your trick?

408
00:29:42,964 --> 00:29:44,864
我讓他殺了我
I let him kill me.

409
00:29:47,064 --> 00:29:50,556
[Door slams shut loudly and locks]

410
00:30:03,914 --> 00:30:07,748
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

411
00:30:38,386 --> 00:30:41,981
你聞起來跟在法庭上一樣糟
LECTER: That's the same atrocious aftershave you wore in court.

412
00:30:43,725 --> 00:30:45,659
古龍水是我每年的聖誕禮物
I keep getting it for Christmas.

413
00:30:45,727 --> 00:30:49,686
對，聖誕節你有收到我的卡片嗎？
LECTER: Christmas, yes. Did you get my card?

414
00:30:51,265 --> 00:30:52,596
有，謝謝
I got it, thank you.

415
00:30:52,667 --> 00:30:56,000
感謝FBI的犯罪實驗室轉寄我的卡片
LECTER: So nice of the Bureau's crime lab to forward that.

416
00:30:57,105 --> 00:31:00,006
他們不給我你的地址
They wouldn't give me your home address.

417
00:31:01,242 --> 00:31:03,938
布魯醫師把你登在《法醫心理學月刊》…
Dr. Bloom sent me your article on surgical addiction...

418
00:31:04,045 --> 00:31:06,513
有關沉迷外科手術的文章寄給我
in the Journal of Forensic Psychiatry.

419
00:31:06,581 --> 00:31:08,208
如何？
LECTER: And?

420
00:31:08,516 --> 00:31:11,076
非常有趣，即使對一個普通人
Very interesting, even to a layman.

421
00:31:16,190 --> 00:31:18,249
你說你是一個普通人
You say you're a layman.

422
00:31:25,566 --> 00:31:29,434
但是你逮到我的，不是嗎？威爾
But it was you who caught me. Wasn't it, Will?

423
00:31:31,272 --> 00:31:35,599
你知道你怎麼辦到的嗎？　　不過是運氣好
LECTER: Do you know how you did it? WILL: I got lucky.

424
00:31:35,710 --> 00:31:38,076
我不覺得你這樣想
I don't think you believe that.

425
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:41,514
已經寫在記錄上了，現在又有什麼關係？
It's in the transcript. What does it matter now?

426
00:31:41,582 --> 00:31:43,914
對我沒關係，威爾
It doesn't matter to me, Will.

427
00:31:44,052 --> 00:31:46,486
我需要你的建議，萊克特醫師
I need your advice, Dr. Lecter.

428
00:31:48,790 --> 00:31:51,054
伯明翰和亞特蘭大
LECTER: Birmingham and Atlanta.

429
00:31:51,726 --> 00:31:54,957
你想知道他為什麼會挑中他們，是不是？
You want to know how he's choosing them, don't you?

430
00:31:55,096 --> 00:31:57,997
我想你有一些想法，我要你告訴我
I thought you'd have ideas. I want you to tell me them.

431
00:31:58,099 --> 00:31:59,430
憑什麼？
Why should I?

432
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:00,899
你缺些東西
There are things you don't have.

433
00:32:00,968 --> 00:32:03,630
調查資料，甚至是計算機
Research materials. Maybe even computer access.

434
00:32:03,738 --> 00:32:05,535
我會和負責人談談
I'd speak to the Chief of Staff.

435
00:32:05,606 --> 00:32:07,574
是，奇爾頓博士
Yes, Dr. Chilton.

436
00:32:08,676 --> 00:32:10,405
他怪可怕的，是不是？
Gruesome, isn't he?

437
00:32:10,478 --> 00:32:12,354
他研究你腦袋的笨拙手段…
He fumbles at your head like a freshman pulling at panties.

438
00:32:12,368 --> 00:32:14,944
就像新鮮人看到女生時笨手笨腳一樣

439
00:32:16,017 --> 00:32:17,678
如果你記得，威爾…
If you recall, Will...

440
00:32:17,752 --> 00:32:20,243
我們最後一次合作的結局挺慘的
our last collaboration ended rather messily.

441
00:32:22,957 --> 00:32:25,619
你可以看到整個案子的檔案
You'd get to see the file on this case.

442
00:32:25,860 --> 00:32:29,421
還有另一個理由   我在聽
- And there's another reason. - I'm all ears.

443
00:32:30,098 --> 00:32:32,498
我以為你會喜歡這個挑戰
I thought you might enjoy the challenge.

444
00:32:32,633 --> 00:32:35,534
發現你比我們在找的人還聰明
Find out if you're smarter than the person I'm looking for.

445
00:32:37,901 --> 00:32:41,393
[Slow, ominous instrumental music]

446
00:32:42,877 --> 00:32:46,643
然後，這樣就表示，你比我聰明…
Then, by implication, you think you're smarter than I am...

447
00:32:46,714 --> 00:32:48,875
因為是你逮到我
since it was you who caught me.

448
00:32:49,016 --> 00:32:50,916
我知道我沒有你聰明
I know I'm not smarter than you.

449
00:32:50,985 --> 00:32:52,919
那你是怎麼逮到我的？
Then how did you catch me?

450
00:32:52,987 --> 00:32:55,512
你有一些缺點
You had disadvantages.

451
00:32:55,857 --> 00:32:57,654
什麼缺點？
What disadvantages?

452
00:32:58,159 --> 00:32:59,786
你瘋了
You're insane.

453
00:33:04,999 --> 00:33:07,126
你曬的很黑，威爾
You're very tanned, Will.

454
00:33:07,368 --> 00:33:10,963
而且你的手很粗，再也不像警察的手
And your hands are so rough. Not like a cop's hands anymore.

455
00:33:11,038 --> 00:33:14,166
你的古龍水聞起來…像是小孩子選的
And that shaving lotion is something a child would select.

456
00:33:14,242 --> 00:33:17,336
有一艘小船在瓶底，對不對？
Has a little ship on the bottle, does it not?

457
00:33:18,012 --> 00:33:20,981
還有你的小喬許和可愛的莫莉都好吧？
And how is young Josh and the lovely Molly?

458
00:33:21,816 --> 00:33:24,216
你知道我常常想到他們
They're always in my thoughts, you know.

459
00:33:24,318 --> 00:33:26,309
你不可能因為我聰明的…
You will not persuade me with appeals...

460
00:33:26,387 --> 00:33:27,854
虛榮心說服我
to my intellectual vanity.

461
00:33:27,922 --> 00:33:29,787
我不覺得我會說服你
I don't think I'll persuade you at all.

462
00:33:29,857 --> 00:33:31,654
你可做可不做
You'll either do it or you won't.

463
00:33:31,726 --> 00:33:34,286
那是這個案子的檔案夾嗎？　　是
LECTER: Is that the case file? WILL: Yes.

464
00:33:34,362 --> 00:33:35,590
有照片嗎？
With photos?

465
00:33:35,663 --> 00:33:37,927
留下來讓我看看，我會考慮考慮
Let me keep them, and I might consider it.

466
00:33:37,999 --> 00:33:39,489
不
No.

467
00:33:42,236 --> 00:33:44,227
威爾，你常作夢嗎？
Do you dream much, Will?

468
00:33:44,338 --> 00:33:45,862
再見，萊克特醫師
Goodbye, Dr. Lecter.

469
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:49,239
你還沒有威脅要把我的書拿走！
You haven't threatened to take away my books yet!

470
00:33:49,410 --> 00:33:51,401
給我檔案！
Give me the file, then!

471
00:33:52,947 --> 00:33:55,347
我會告訴你我的想法
And I'll tell you what I think.

472
00:33:57,952 --> 00:34:00,420
我需要獨處一個小時
I'll need one hour. And privacy.

473
00:34:07,195 --> 00:34:09,527
就像以前一樣威爾？
Just like old times, Will?

474
00:34:10,728 --> 00:34:14,220
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

475
00:34:39,460 --> 00:34:41,951
他是一個非常害羞的男孩，威爾
LECTER: This is a very shy boy, Will.

476
00:34:42,296 --> 00:34:44,059
我希望能見見他
I'd love to meet him.

477
00:34:44,131 --> 00:34:47,225
你有沒有想過他可能是破相…
Have you considered that he is disfigured...

478
00:34:47,301 --> 00:34:49,428
或他以為自己是破相？
or that he may believe he is disfigured?

479
00:34:49,503 --> 00:34:51,061
對，鏡子
Yeah, the mirrors.

480
00:34:51,138 --> 00:34:53,106
注意到他砸壞所有的鏡子…
Notice he smashes all the mirrors...

481
00:34:53,174 --> 00:34:55,301
不只為了那些碎片
not just enough to get the pieces he wants.

482
00:34:55,409 --> 00:34:57,707
當然還有放在眼睛裡的碎片…
And, of course, those shards in their eyes...

483
00:34:57,778 --> 00:34:59,177
所以他能看見自己
so he can see himself there.

484
00:34:59,247 --> 00:35:00,441
很有趣
That's interesting.

485
00:35:00,514 --> 00:35:02,675
不，你已經這樣想過了
No, it's not. You thought of it before.

486
00:35:03,317 --> 00:35:05,217
我是這樣想過
I had considered it.

487
00:35:05,286 --> 00:35:07,413
那些女人呢？　　死了？
- What about the women? - Dead?

488
00:35:07,488 --> 00:35:09,046
只是布偶
Mere puppets.

489
00:35:09,123 --> 00:35:12,756
你必須看她們活著的時候…她們吸引他的地方
You need to see them living, the way they caught his eye.

490
00:35:12,793 --> 00:35:14,021
不可能
That's impossible.

491
00:35:14,095 --> 00:35:16,063
幾乎是，但不盡然
Almost. Not quite.

492
00:35:17,531 --> 00:35:19,624
院子是什麼樣子？
What were the yards like?

493
00:35:20,668 --> 00:35:24,695
大後院有籬笆，有一些是樹籬，為何這樣問？
Big backyards, fenced, some hedges. Why?

494
00:35:25,139 --> 00:35:26,629
因為若這是朝聖…
Because if this pilgrim...

495
00:35:26,707 --> 00:35:28,800
感覺和月亮有某種特別關係…
feels a special relationship with the moon...

496
00:35:28,876 --> 00:35:31,674
他可能喜歡走到戶外看一看
he might like to go outside and look at it.

497
00:35:31,779 --> 00:35:33,713
你有在月光下看過血嗎？
You ever seen blood in the moonlight?

498
00:35:33,781 --> 00:35:35,715
顏色挺黑的
It appears quite black.

499
00:35:35,950 --> 00:35:39,442
假設有人沒穿衣服，最好是有…
If one were nude, say, it'd be better to have...

500
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:41,681
戶外的隱私，對那樣的事…
outdoor privacy for that sort of thing.

501
00:35:42,323 --> 00:35:45,121
你認為院子是他挑選下手對象的考慮因素？
You think the yards are a factor when he selects victims?

502
00:35:45,192 --> 00:35:46,591
對
Yes.

503
00:35:46,661 --> 00:35:50,062
而且…當然不只這些受害者
And there will be more of them, of course. Victims.

504
00:35:51,365 --> 00:35:53,765
這樣談話的機會將越來越多…
You'll be wanting lots of these little chinwags...

505
00:35:53,834 --> 00:35:55,563
我接了   我不一定有時間
- I take it. - I might not have time.

506
00:35:55,636 --> 00:35:57,001
我有
I do.

507
00:35:57,071 --> 00:35:58,629
我多的是時間
I have oodles.

508
00:35:58,706 --> 00:36:00,765
現在我要聽聽你的意見
I need your opinion now.

509
00:36:00,841 --> 00:36:02,502
第一…
Then here's one:

510
00:36:03,010 --> 00:36:06,379
在你廉價的古龍水之下…是你發臭的恐懼
You stink of fear under that cheap lotion.

511
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:10,745
你的恐懼發臭，威爾，但你不是一個懦夫！
You stink of fear, Will, but you're not a coward!

512
00:36:11,352 --> 00:36:13,343
你怕我，但是你還是來找我
You fear me, but still you came here.

513
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:17,913
你怕那個害羞的男孩，但你還是會把他找出來
You fear this shy boy, yet still you seek him out.

514
00:36:19,927 --> 00:36:22,088
威爾，你不懂嗎？
