01:19:55,540 --> 01:19:59,203
有沒有人覺得…他的動作太快了？
Does it strike anybody that he set this up in a hurry?

1195
01:19:59,311 --> 01:20:01,711
報紙刊登的時間是星期一晚上
The Tattler comes off the press Monday night.

1196
01:20:01,813 --> 01:20:05,305
星期二早上，他就到芝加哥來堵勞茲
By Tuesday morning he's in Chicago, snatching Lounds.

1197
01:20:05,383 --> 01:20:07,374
他要不住在芝加哥…
He either lives in the Chicago area...

1198
01:20:07,452 --> 01:20:09,886
就是住在車程六個小時之內…
or he's within a driving radius of...

1199
01:20:09,988 --> 01:20:11,819
可以到的地方
call it six hours.

1200
01:20:11,890 --> 01:20:14,552
在這樣的範圍之內找到《傳聞報》…
Find out in this area where the Tattler was available...

1201
01:20:14,659 --> 01:20:16,650
在星期一晚上的配送地點
for early distribution Monday night.

1202
01:20:16,728 --> 01:20:18,593
從機場夜間報攤開始
Start with airports, all-night newsstands.

1203
01:20:18,663 --> 01:20:20,756
也許一些報販會記得奇怪的客人
Maybe a newsie remembers an odd customer.

1204
01:20:20,832 --> 01:20:22,925
羅伊，加強這個卡帶聲音的部份
Lloyd, this cassette, enhance the audio.

1205
01:20:23,001 --> 01:20:25,731
也許你可以聽到些背景的聲音
Maybe you can pick up something in the background.

1206
01:20:25,837 --> 01:20:27,099
輪椅…
That wheelchair...

1207
01:20:27,172 --> 01:20:29,265
我要製造商、日期、可能的數據
I want the maker, date, possible sources.

1208
01:20:29,341 --> 01:20:33,072
葛蘭姆和我會坐鎮在芝加哥，快展開行動
Graham and I will coordinate from Chicago. Let's hustle.

1209
01:20:45,190 --> 01:20:48,887
聽著，傑克，在芝加哥找不到答案的
Look, there's not gonna be any answers in Chicago, Jack.

1210
01:20:49,561 --> 01:20:52,587
我是說，勞茲只是個意外
Okay? I mean, Lounds, that was a bonus.

1211
01:20:53,331 --> 01:20:57,700
他不過是在炫耀…跟他慣用的手法完全不一樣
That was a chance to show off. It doesn't even fit his pattern.

1212
01:20:58,670 --> 01:21:01,662
立茲和傑柯比一家…才是他要的
The Leeds and the Jacobis are what he needs.

1213
01:21:08,680 --> 01:21:10,671
我覺得我應該回去巴爾的摩
I think I should go back to Baltimore.

1214
01:21:10,749 --> 01:21:12,307
在他想殺你之後？
After what he tried to pull?

1215
01:21:12,384 --> 01:21:15,751
萊克特在紙條遺失的部分得到線索
Lecter picked up on something in the missing part of the note.

1216
01:21:15,854 --> 01:21:18,448
不是名字，是某個可以把搜尋範圍縮小的東西
Not a name, but something, enough to narrow the search.

1217
01:21:18,523 --> 01:21:20,320
即使他有也不會告訴你
Even if he did, he won't tell you.

1218
01:21:20,392 --> 01:21:22,417
除非我可以給他什麼
Not unless I can offer him something.

1219
01:21:23,261 --> 01:21:25,024
恭喜，威爾
LECTER [Voice-over]: Congratulations.

1220
01:21:25,096 --> 01:21:29,863
你把勞茲弄走的方法真是高明啊
That was most artistic, the way you disposed of Mr. Lounds.

1221
01:21:30,435 --> 01:21:32,665
書本移走了，你的牢房看起來大多了
Your cell looks bigger with no books in it.

1222
01:21:32,737 --> 01:21:33,704
是嗎？
Does it?

1223
01:21:33,772 --> 01:21:35,399
我倒是沒注意到
I hadn't noticed.

1224
01:21:35,473 --> 01:21:36,838
你會
WILL: Oh, you will.

1225
01:21:36,908 --> 01:21:38,899
我有其它的消息來源
I have other resources.

1226
01:21:40,278 --> 01:21:42,769
告訴我，威爾，你樂在其中嗎？
Tell me, Will. Did you enjoy it?

1227
01:21:43,715 --> 01:21:45,580
你的第一樁謀殺？
Your first murder?

1228
01:21:45,650 --> 01:21:48,050
當然，這樣的感覺怎麼會不好？
Of course you did. Why shouldn't it feel good?

1229
01:21:48,119 --> 01:21:50,019
對上帝是好的
It does to God.

1230
01:21:50,622 --> 01:21:53,819
嗯，上周在德州…他弄垮教堂屋頂…
Why, only last week in Texas, he dropped a church roof...

1231
01:21:53,925 --> 01:21:56,223
砸在34個祈禱者的頭上…
on the heads of 34 of his worshippers...

1232
01:21:56,294 --> 01:21:58,524
當他們正在聖歌前卑躬屈膝時
as they were groveling through a hymn.

1233
01:21:58,596 --> 01:22:01,463
他不會吝惜一個記者
He wouldn't begrudge you one journalist.

1234
01:22:01,733 --> 01:22:03,325
讓他來找我，醫生
Put me next to him, Doctor.

1235
01:22:03,401 --> 01:22:05,028
你和你的迅雷小組？
You and some SWAT team?

1236
01:22:05,103 --> 01:22:07,663
哦，威爾，那有什麼樂趣呢？
Oh, Will. Where's the fun in that?

1237
01:22:07,906 --> 01:22:10,500
他也要碰運氣
He'll have to take his chances, too.

1238
01:22:10,675 --> 01:22:12,973
意外可能發生在任何人身上
A roof can fall on anybody.

1239
01:22:14,345 --> 01:22:16,779
但是不會在莫莉和喬許身上
But not on Molly and Josh, I take it.

1240
01:22:16,848 --> 01:22:18,816
還沒發生就是了
Not yet, anyway.

1241
01:22:19,184 --> 01:22:22,119
首先他殺掉寵物，然後是一家人
First he kills the pet, then the family.

1242
01:22:23,021 --> 01:22:24,989
佛雷迪是你的寵物
Freddy was your pet.

1243
01:22:25,290 --> 01:22:26,917
他們現在很安全
They're safe now.

1244
01:22:26,991 --> 01:22:29,551
在你身邊的人沒一個是安全的，威爾
No one will ever be safe around you, Will.

1245
01:22:30,524 --> 01:22:34,358
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

1246
01:22:39,804 --> 01:22:42,364
不過解碼倒是解得很聰明
Clever work on his note, by the way.

1247
01:22:42,474 --> 01:22:45,637
斷電那部份也相當不錯
And that blackout was an especially nice touch.

1248
01:22:46,811 --> 01:22:49,371
醫生，紙條上還說了什麼？
What else was in that note, Doctor?

1249
01:22:53,451 --> 01:22:55,214
讓他來找我！
Put me next to him!

1250
01:22:55,720 --> 01:22:57,449
那不就是你想要的？
That's what you want, isn't it?

1251
01:22:57,522 --> 01:22:59,285
讓他幫助你完成
To help him succeed where you failed?

1252
01:22:59,357 --> 01:23:00,915
你想失敗兩次？
Twice?

1253
01:23:00,992 --> 01:23:03,290
給他一個殺我的機會
Give him a chance to kill me.

1254
01:23:04,395 --> 01:23:05,828
繼續
Go on, then.

1255
01:23:05,897 --> 01:23:08,127
使出你的看家本領打動我
Seduce me with your wares.

1256
01:23:08,399 --> 01:23:10,799
全面恢復你原本享有的特權
Full restoration of your privileges.

1257
01:23:10,869 --> 01:23:13,736
外加在監控之下一星期一次…
Plus computer access to the AMA archives.

1258
01:23:13,838 --> 01:23:16,500
使用計算機進入美國醫藥協會檔案
One hour a week under supervision, of course...

1259
01:23:16,574 --> 01:23:17,871
但機會只有一次
but it's a one-time offer.

1260
01:23:17,942 --> 01:23:20,308
一旦我離開這裡條件就失效
It expires the minute I walk out of here.

1261
01:23:20,378 --> 01:23:22,005
太小氣了，不是嗎？
Bit measly, don't you think?

1262
01:23:22,080 --> 01:23:26,210
拒絕我啊，看看你可以從奇爾頓那裡得到什麼
Turn it down, then. See what terms you get from Chilton.

1263
01:23:26,484 --> 01:23:28,008
威爾，你在威脅我嗎？
Are these threats, William?

1264
01:23:28,086 --> 01:23:32,079
我在等你，醫生，也許你根本沒什麼好跟我交換
I'm waiting, Doctor. Or maybe you've got nothing left to sell.

1265
01:23:36,027 --> 01:23:38,894
一個小樣本，為什麼不？
A little sample, then. Why not?

1266
01:23:39,764 --> 01:23:41,755
你看過佈雷克的書了嗎？　　看過
- Seen the Blake, have you? - Yes.

1267
01:23:41,833 --> 01:23:43,824
不，你看了但沒有看進去
No, you've looked but not seen.

1268
01:23:43,902 --> 01:23:45,836
轉型是關鍵
Transformation is the key.

1269
01:23:45,904 --> 01:23:47,769
所謂的人龍…
The man-dragon...

1270
01:23:47,872 --> 01:23:50,432
他的醜陋藉由力量轉型
his ugliness transformed by power.

1271
01:23:50,742 --> 01:23:53,768
在軍隊的資料中找找看，受過格鬥訓練的人
Look for a military record with combat training.

1272
01:23:53,878 --> 01:23:55,937
有大面積刺青的人…
Look for extensive tattooing...

1273
01:23:56,047 --> 01:23:58,311
還有做過矯正手術，特別是在臉部
and corrective surgery, most likely to the face.

1274
01:23:58,383 --> 01:24:01,875
拜託這些我都知道了
Come on, I'm past that already and you know it.

1275
01:24:02,253 --> 01:24:03,652
說些有用的
Give me what I need.

1276
01:24:03,721 --> 01:24:05,313
他選女人的條件？
How is he choosing the women?

1277
01:24:05,390 --> 01:24:08,416
我已經告訴你了，答案就在你眼前
I've already suggested how. The answer was in front of you.

1278
01:24:08,526 --> 01:24:10,203
你看到了，但沒看進去
- You looked but didn't see. - Bullshit! No riddles!

1279
01:24:10,226 --> 01:24:11,823
放屁！別跟我玩猜謎！

1280
01:24:11,863 --> 01:24:13,057
直接告訴我
Just tell me.

1281
01:24:13,131 --> 01:24:14,155
不！
No!

1282
01:24:14,232 --> 01:24:15,221
你自找的
LECTER: It's your turn.

1283
01:24:15,300 --> 01:24:17,700
我上次禮貌的要求你…
I asked you before for a small courtesy...

1284
01:24:17,769 --> 01:24:19,930
可是你卻粗魯的回絕我
and you responded rudely.

1285
01:24:21,206 --> 01:24:22,969
在我透露更多內容以前…
Before I tell you anything more...

1286
01:24:23,041 --> 01:24:26,067
你要為我安排一些特別節目
you will make certain arrangements for me.

1287
01:24:26,377 --> 01:24:28,368
什麼特別節目？
What kind of arrangements?

1288
01:24:28,446 --> 01:24:30,209
哦，很簡單
Oh, nothing much.

1289
01:24:30,949 --> 01:24:33,315
我們叫它晚餐秀怎麼樣？
Shall we say dinner and a show?

1290
01:24:36,788 --> 01:24:39,985
你準備要告訴我…我們要去哪裡了嗎？
You ready to tell me what kind of outing this is?

1291
01:24:40,892 --> 01:24:42,450
還沒
Nope.

1292
01:24:43,294 --> 01:24:46,388
杜，你就是充滿驚奇，是不是？
You're just full of surprises, aren't you, D?

1293
01:24:47,131 --> 01:24:48,621
對
Yep.

1294
01:24:50,335 --> 01:24:52,098
他離你大約兩公尺
WARFIELD: He's about six feet away.

1295
01:24:52,170 --> 01:24:54,138
你聞得到他嗎？
Can you smell him?

1296
01:24:54,239 --> 01:24:55,228
可以
Yeah.

1297
01:24:55,306 --> 01:24:58,833
現在他有一點吵，但我保證他非常鎮靜
Now, he's a little noisy, but he's sedated, I assure you.

1298
01:24:59,677 --> 01:25:02,237
海斯勒醫生準備要修復他斷掉的牙齒
Doctor Hassler's about to fix his broken tooth.

1299
01:25:02,313 --> 01:25:04,042
很高興你能來，麥克蓮小姐
Glad you could come, Ms. McClane.

1300
01:25:04,115 --> 01:25:06,743
非常謝謝你的紅外線底片
We appreciate the infrared film, by the way.

1301
01:25:06,818 --> 01:25:08,718
往前再走兩步
WARFIELD: Two more steps.

1302
01:25:08,987 --> 01:25:12,252
我會把你的左手放在桌子的邊緣
I'll put your left hand on the edge of the table.

1303
01:25:13,291 --> 01:25:15,259
現在他就在你面前
Now, he's right in front of you.

1304
01:25:15,326 --> 01:25:16,953
慢慢來
Take your time.

1305
01:25:22,163 --> 01:25:24,654
[Tiger bays drowsily]

1306
01:25:24,335 --> 01:25:27,699
我在這裡
- D? - I'm here.

1307
01:25:28,940 --> 01:25:30,498
別怕
You go ahead.

1308
01:25:32,640 --> 01:25:36,132
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

1309
01:25:45,820 --> 01:25:49,153
[Tiger growls sleepily]

1310
01:26:15,420 --> 01:26:17,115
就在這裡
Here.

1311
01:26:18,990 --> 01:26:21,015
你聽聽看這個？
Why don't you try this?

1312
01:26:34,235 --> 01:26:37,398
[Strong heartbeat]

1313
01:27:00,494 --> 01:27:03,486
[Clock ticking]

1314
01:27:07,238 --> 01:27:09,968
從前門走九步碰到時鐘…
Nine steps from the front door to the clock...

1315
01:27:10,074 --> 01:27:12,042
再走三步就到客廳
and three more to this room.

1316
01:27:13,277 --> 01:27:15,211
對不起，這是習慣
Sorry. Force of habit.

1317
01:27:21,552 --> 01:27:24,715
那頭漂亮的老虎，這個房子還有音樂…
[Jazz music plays]

1318
01:27:22,683 --> 01:27:26,016
That beautiful tiger, this house, this music....

1319
01:27:25,723 --> 01:27:28,658
杜，我不覺得有人真的瞭解你
I don't think anybody knows you at all, D.

1320
01:27:28,793 --> 01:27:30,988
不過每個人都在談你
Everybody wonders about you, though.

1321
01:27:31,095 --> 01:27:32,960
特別是女人
Especially the women.

1322
01:27:33,731 --> 01:27:35,528
她們想知道什麼？
What do they want to know?

1323
01:27:35,600 --> 01:27:37,227
她們覺得你…
They find you...

1324
01:27:37,301 --> 01:27:39,895
非常神秘又有趣
very mysterious and interesting.

1325
01:27:44,008 --> 01:27:46,533
她們有沒有告訴你我長什麼樣子？
Did they tell you how I look?

1326
01:27:46,611 --> 01:27:50,069
她們說你的體格很棒
They said that you have a remarkable body.

1327
01:27:51,949 --> 01:27:56,079
你對你的長相非常敏感，但其實你不用擔心
That you're very sensitive about your face but you shouldn't be.

1328
01:27:56,954 --> 01:27:58,717
哦，還有…
Oh, and...

1329
01:28:00,591 --> 01:28:02,582
她們問我…
they asked me if...

1330
01:28:03,294 --> 01:28:05,990
你是不是和外表看起來一樣挺拔
you are as strong as you look.

1331
01:28:07,432 --> 01:28:09,059
還有？
And?

1332
01:28:10,234 --> 01:28:12,099
我說我不知道
I said I didn't know.

1333
01:28:16,303 --> 01:28:18,464
[Record stops playing]

1334
01:28:36,890 --> 01:28:40,382
[Seductive jazz music plays]

1335
01:28:48,706 --> 01:28:50,867
杜，你在哪裡？
Where the hell are you, D?

1336
01:28:56,781 --> 01:28:58,476
你在這裡
Here you are.

1337
01:29:02,954 --> 01:29:05,889
你想知道我怎麼想的嗎？
Do you want to know what I think about it?

1338
01:29:28,312 --> 01:29:31,372
你可以告訴我洗手間在哪裡嗎？
Now, would you show me where the bathroom is?

1339
01:29:42,589 --> 01:29:46,081
[Slow, suspenseful instrumental music]

1340
01:29:55,602 --> 01:29:59,094
[Seductive jazz music plays]

1341
01:30:04,682 --> 01:30:06,843
我有點事要做
I have to do a little work.

1342
01:30:07,919 --> 01:30:10,786
如果我耽誤你的時間…　　沒有
- If I'm keeping you from work... - No.

1343
01:30:10,888 --> 01:30:13,448
我還是離開好了   我要你留下來
- ...I'll go. - I want you to be here.

1344
01:30:13,591 --> 01:30:16,389
真的，我只需要看一卷錄像帶
I do. It's just a tape I need to watch.

1345
01:30:17,228 --> 01:30:19,253
但是不會花太多時間
It won't take long.

1346
01:30:27,038 --> 01:30:30,201
你需要聽到聲音嗎？　　不用
- Do you need to hear it, too? - No.

1347
01:30:30,308 --> 01:30:32,276
讓音樂繼續好嗎？
May I keep the music?

1348
01:31:20,954 --> 01:31:24,788
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

1349
01:31:33,938 --> 01:31:35,963
關於什麼的錄像帶？
What's it about?

1350
01:31:37,441 --> 01:31:39,773
一些我即將見面的人
Some people I'm going to meet.

1351
01:31:50,488 --> 01:31:52,115
所以…
So then...

1352
01:31:53,791 --> 01:31:55,787
是什麼？是企業的宣傳
it's what? It's a corporate promo? Some kind of homework?

1353
01:31:55,811 --> 01:31:58,887
一些要在家先準備好的功課？

1354
01:32:00,865 --> 01:32:04,062
對
It's homework. Yeah.

1355
01:32:09,674 --> 01:32:11,471
好主意
That's a good idea.

1356
01:32:13,344 --> 01:32:15,835
事先準備是非常重要的
It's so important to be prepared.

1357
01:32:21,886 --> 01:32:24,855
我的天，你真的！
My God, are you ever!

1358
01:32:27,054 --> 01:32:30,546
[Dramatic instrumental music]

1359
01:33:14,601 --> 01:33:18,093
[Tense instrumental music]

1360
01:33:50,437 --> 01:33:53,929
[Dolarhyde whimpers in panic]

1361
01:33:59,083 --> 01:34:01,950
不，我不會把她給你，不
DOLARHYDE: No. I won't give her to you. No.

1362
01:34:03,150 --> 01:34:06,642
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

1363
01:34:12,963 --> 01:34:16,797
求求你，只要一下下
Please, just for a little while.

1364
01:34:24,441 --> 01:34:26,432
不，你在傷害我！
[Crying] No! You're hurting me!

1365
01:34:45,726 --> 01:34:49,389
[Dramatic instrumental music]

1366
01:34:48,332 --> 01:34:49,890
不…
No...

1367
01:34:50,734 --> 01:34:52,429
她人很好
she's nice.

1368
01:34:53,637 --> 01:34:55,400
她沒問題的
She's okay.

1369
01:35:01,641 --> 01:35:05,133
[Climactic instrumental music]

1370
01:35:25,369 --> 01:35:27,865
